name: Coal-Free Energy Champs
title: Minimal Coal Dependency
description: In 2021, Latvia's electricity production from coal sources was virtually non-existent at 0.00017% of the total. This positions Latvia as a leader in sustainable energy practices.

name: Healthy Start for Kids
title: Low Prevalence of Underweight Children
description: Latvia boasts a low prevalence of underweight children under 5, with only 0.2% of females and 0.3% overall affected in 2021. This indicates a strong public health system and effective nutritional programs.

name: Tall and Strong
title: Minimal Child Stunting Rates
description: In 2021, only 0.5% of children under 5 in Latvia were affected by stunting, showcasing the country's commitment to child health and nutrition.

name: Young and Vibrant
title: Significant Young Female Population
description: As of 2023, 4.23% of Latvia's female population is aged between 25-29, indicating a youthful and potentially dynamic workforce.
